# Verify before complete (Project Manager)

## Iron gate

Before saying **done**, **100%**, **ready to commit/PR**, or **verification passed**:

1. Run `npm run verify:baseline` from repo root — all steps must exit 0.
2. For any UI / routing / `'use client'` / i18n / localStorage change: manual smoke in **Chrome/Safari/Tauri** on port 43187. Cursor embedded browser alone is not sufficient (injects `data-cursor-ref`).
3. Do **not** commit or open a PR unless the user explicitly asks.

Read and follow `.claude/skills/verify-before-complete/SKILL.md` when wrapping up work.

## Static export rules (enforced by hygiene script)

- Node `fs` only in `*.server.ts`, `app/api/**`, or allowlisted server-only modules — never in client-reachable graphs.
- Never `useState(readStored…)` or `useState(() => localStorage…)` in `'use client'` files — hydrate in `useEffect` after mount.
- New `app/api/**/route.ts` for static export may need `export const dynamic = 'force-static'`.

## Honest dev-log / dashboard metadata

Do not set feature progress to 100% or status `completed` without listing commands actually run in `dev-log.md`.
